%20as%20his%20government's%20%26quot%3Bnumber%20one%20mission%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Labour%20leader%20on%20Friday%20won%20a%20landslide%20election%20victory%20bringing%20to%20a%20close%2014%20years%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Brestless%20for%20change%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20his%20party%20had%20received%20a%20%26quot%3Bmandate%20to%20do%20politics%20differently%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeir%20Starmer%20started%20the%20day%20with%20a%20first%20meeting%20of%20his%20cabinet%20including%20Britain's%20first%20woman%20finance%20minister%20Rachel%20Reeves%20and%20new%20foreign%20minister%20David%20Lammy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20work%20to%20do%2C%20so%20now%20we%20get%20on%20with%20our%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20his%20top%20team%20to%20applause%20and%20smiles%20around%20the%20cabinet%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20news%20conference%20afterwards%20he%20said%20he%20would%20not%20be%20proceeding%20with%20former%20Conservative%20prime%20minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20controversial%20scheme%20to%20tackle%20rising%20small%20boat%20arrivals%20on%20England's%20southern%20coast%20by%20deporting%20migrants%20to%20Rwanda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Rwanda%20scheme%20was%20dead%20and%20buried%20before%20it%20started...%20I'm%20not%20prepared%20to%20continue%20with%20gimmicks%20that%20don't%20act%20as%20a%20deterrent%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters%20at%20his%2010%20Downing%20Street%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Driving%20growth'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeir%20Starmer%20spent%20his%20first%20hours%20in%20Downing%20Street%20on%20Friday%20appointing%20his%20ministerial%20team%2C%20hours%20after%20securing%20his%20centre-left%20party's%20return%20to%20power%20with%20a%20whopping%20174-seat%20majority%20in%20the%20UK%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotable%20lower-ranking%20appointments%20included%20Patrick%20Vallance%2C%20chief%20scientific%20government%20adviser%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20who%20has%20been%20made%20a%20science%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJames%20Timpson%2C%20whose%20shoe%20repair%20company%20employs%20ex-offenders%2C%20was%20also%20made%20a%20prisons%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeir%20Starmer%20said%20both%20new%20ministers%20were%20people%20%26quot%3Bassociated%20with%20change%26quot%3B%20and%20illustrated%20his%20determination%20to%20deliver%20concrete%20improvements%20to%20people's%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWork%20on%20%26quot%3Bdriving%20growth%26quot%3B%20had%20already%20begun%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20had%20told%20his%20ministers%20%26quot%3Bexactly%20what%20I%20expect%20of%20them%20in%20terms%20of%20standards%2C%20delivery%2C%20and%20the%20trust%20that%20the%20country%20has%20put%20in%20them%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENATO%20support%20'unshakable'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlag-waving%20crowds%20of%20cheering%20Labour%20activists%20on%20Friday%20welcomed%20Keir%20Starmer%20to%20Downing%20Street%20hours%20after%20his%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20daunting%20challenges%20await%20his%20government%2C%20including%20a%20stagnating%20economy%2C%20creaking%20public%20services%20and%20households%20suffering%20from%20a%20years-long%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorld%20leaders%20lined%20up%20to%20congratulate%20the%20new%20British%20premier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeir%20Starmer%20spoke%20by%20telephone%20with%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20%26quot%3Bdiscussed%20their%20shared%20commitment%20to%20the%20special%20relationship%20between%20the%20UK%20and%20US%20and%20their%20aligned%20ambitions%20for%20greater%20economic%20growth%26quot%3B%2C%20according%20to%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20spoke%20to%20President%20of%20the%20European%20Commission%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%2C%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%2C%20and%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20former%20--%20and%20potentially%20future%20--%20US%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20ignored%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20instead%20hailing%20the%20five-seat%20electoral%20breakthrough%20of%20his%20ally%20Nigel%20Farage's%20far-right%20Reform%20UK%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeir%20Starmer%20will%20make%20his%20debut%20on%20the%20international%20stage%20as%20leader%20when%20he%20flies%20to%20Washington%20next%20week%20for%20a%20NATO%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20for%20me%20to%20be%20absolutely%20clear%20that%20the%20first%20duty%20of%20my%20government%20is%20security%20and%20defence%2C%20to%20make%20clear%20our%20unshakable%20support%20of%20Nato%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20had%20reiterated%20the%20support%20of%20the%20UK%20and%20its%20allies%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20Zelensky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInfighting%20fears%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20saw%20Labour%20near%20its%20record%20of%20418%20seats%20under%20ex-leader%20Tony%20Blair%20in%201997%20by%20winning%20412.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Conservatives%20suffered%20their%20worst-ever%20defeat%2C%20capturing%20just%20121%20constituencies%2C%20prompting%20Rishi%20Sunak%20to%20apologise%20to%20the%20nation%20and%20confirm%20that%20he%20will%20resign%20as%20Tory%20leader%20once%20arrangements%20are%20in%20place%20to%20select%20a%20successor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20record%2012%20senior%20ex-government%20ministers%20lost%20their%20seats%2C%20alongside%20former%20prime%20minister%20Liz%20Truss%2C%20whose%20economically%20calamitous%20short-lived%20tenure%20in%202022%20wounded%20the%20party%20irreparably%20ahead%20of%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20now%20poised%20for%20another%20period%20of%20infighting%20between%20a%20moderate%20wing%20eager%20for%20a%20centrist%20leader%20and%20those%20who%20may%20even%20be%20willing%20to%20court%20Farage%20as%20a%20new%20figurehead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn