Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETorre%20Guinigi%20in%20Lucca%2C%20Italy%2C%20is%20home%20to%20a%20unique%20rooftop%20garden.%3Cp%3EMaremagnum%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETorre%20Guinigi%2C%20or%20Guinigi%20Tower%2C%20was%20built%20in%20Lucca%2C%20Italy%2C%20in%20the%20late%201300s.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20common%20for%20wealthy%20families%20to%20commission%20towers%20to%20see%20who%20could%20build%20the%20tallest%20one.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20tower's%20roof%20has%20a%20garden%2C%20which%20has%20several%20tall%20holm%20oak%20trees%20and%20is%20open%20to%20visitors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20homeowners'%20displays%20of%20wealth%20might%20include%20at-home%20movie%20theaters%2C%20helipads%2C%20sprawling%20subterranean%20garages%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fluxury-home-products-worth-splurging-on-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etowel%20warmer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20medieval%20Italy%2C%20homeowners%20were%20more%20obvious%3A%20The%20taller%20their%20structure%2C%20they%20thought%2C%20the%20greater%20their%20wealth%20and%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rich%20sought%20to%20one-up%20each%20other%20by%20building%20the%20tallest%20towers%20they%20could.%20In%20some%20cities%2C%20like%20Lucca%20in%20Tuscany%2C%20the%20competition%20led%20to%20a%20skyline%20of%20medieval%20skyscrapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20Lucca%20today%2C%20just%20two%20towers%20remain%20from%20the%20time%20period%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.turismo.lucca.it%2Fen%2Ftorre-delle-ore%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecity's%20tourism%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20is%20Torre%20Guinigi%2C%20or%20Guinigi%20Tower%2C%20which%20was%20built%20in%20the%2014th%20century.%20Beyond%20its%20fascinating%20history%2C%20it's%20also%20notable%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeautiful-gardens-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunique%20rooftop%20garden%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20oak%20trees%2C%20which%20is%20visible%20from%20the%20street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20tower%2C%20its%20history%2C%20and%20the%20spectacular%20views%20offered%20from%20its%20garden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20150-foot-tall%20Torre%20Guinigi%20dominates%20the%20skyline%20in%20Lucca%2C%20a%20city%20in%20Tuscany%2C%20Italy.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222126%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Torre%20Guinigi%20is%20significantly%20taller%20than%20the%20buildings%20around%20it%20in%20Lucca%2C%20Italy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6685b6801aace5b3ada4654e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETorre%20Guinigi%20stands%20above%20other%20buildings%20in%20Lucca%2C%20Tuscany.%3Cp%3EMarian%20Bulacu%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20medieval%20tower%2C%20an%20example%20of%20Romanesque-Gothic%20architecture%2C%20was%20built%20in%20the%20late%2014th%20century%20for%20a%20family%20of%20wealthy%20merchants%20and%20bankers%2C%20the%20Guinigis.%20It%20was%20part%20of%20a%20complex%20of%20buildings%20where%20members%20of%20the%20family%20lived%2C%20according%20to%20the%20tower's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcultura.comune.lucca.it%2FtorreGuinigi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisitor%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20the%20city%20had%20more%20than%20130%20towers.%20Today%2C%20according%20to%20the%20city's%20tourism%20office%2C%20Torre%20Guinigi%20is%20one%20of%20just%20two%20towers%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20Middle%20Ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAt%20the%20time%20it%20was%20built%2C%20neighbors%20competed%20to%20see%20who%20could%20build%20the%20tallest%20structure.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223884%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20among%20the%20trees%20o