unds%20are%20in%20it%20or%20how%20the%20money%20is%20being%20invested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20with%20certified%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkovarwealth.com%2Ftaylor-kovar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaylor%20Kovar%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20find%20out%20what%20I%20can%20do%20to%20put%20this%20money%20on%20a%20better%20path%20for%20growth%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274c015c6-6b41-4bcc-9dd0-38192e3016e9%5C%22%3E1.%20Understand%20what's%20in%20your%20retirement%20account%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20people%20I%20know%20actively%20manage%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20move%20money%20between%20different%20funds%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%2C%20I%20don't%20touch%20my%20accounts%20and%20let%20them%20be%20passively%20managed%20by%20the%20brokerage.%20I%20don't%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20the%20knowledge%20or%20time%20to%20be%20able%20to%20manage%20my%20retirement%20accounts%20on%20my%20own.%20However%2C%20Kovar%20said%20it's%20still%20important%20to%20keep%20a%20pulse%20on%20what's%20happening%20inside%20of%20those%20retirement%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20know%20what%20your%20money%20is%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20your%20employer%20has%20changed%20up%20some%20of%20the%20options%20or%20your%20funds%20are%20taking%20a%20low-risk%20path%20and%20not%20providing%20you%20with%20growth.%20Either%20way%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20know%20so%20you're%20not%20missing%20out%20on%20opportunities%20to%20enhance%20your%20wealth%20and%20have%20better%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20auditing%20my%20retirement%20account%20to%20make%20sure%20my%20investments%20aren't%20carrying%20high%20fees%2C%20using%20a%20free%20portfolio%20analyzer%20to%20spot%20hidden%20fees%2C%20staying%20informed%20and%20educated%2C%20or%20chatting%20with%20a%20financial%20advisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKovar%20noticed%20that%20my%20money%20was%20allocated%20well%20between%20diversified%20funds%20(ex%3A%20international%20exposure%2C%20emerging%20markets)%20but%20there%20could%20be%20room%20for%20improvement%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20changing%20risk%20exposure%2C%20adding%20more%20of%20a%20mix%20of%20ETFs%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmutual-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20types%20of%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20rushing%20to%20make%20any%20changes%2C%20take%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20understand%20why%20you%20are%20making%20the%20change.%20What%20goal%20are%20you%20working%20toward%20and%20why%20do%20you%20feel%20you%20need%20to%20make%20a%20change%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPlus%2C%20remember%2C%20just%20because%20a%20certain%20investment%20worked%20for%20someone%20else%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20it%20will%20automatically%20work%20for%20you!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22524ad843-25b9-4792-9024-7f506a4ae604%5C%22%3E2.%20Check%20on%20your%20risk%20levels%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKovar%20said%20the%20mix%20of%20investments%20that%20often%20make%20up%20a%20retirement%20account%20can%20range%20based%20on%20what%20level%20of%20risk%20you're%20the%20most%20comfortable%20with.%20People%20looking%20for%20more%20risk%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20might%20want%20to%20have%20fewer%20bonds%20in%20their%20account%20and%20more%20stocks.%20Those%20who%20are%20inching%20closer%20to%20retirement%20and%20are%20more%20risk-averse%20might%20want%20to%20have%20more%20bonds%20in%20their%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20mentioned%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20increase%20my%20risk%20and%20retire%20early%2C%20he%20recommended%20dropping%20bond%20funds%20entirely%20and%20utilizing%20additional%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-etf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EETFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20market%20segments%20I%20like%2C%20such%20as%20energy%2C%20technology%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20will%20this%20help%20diversify%20you%20more%2C%20it%20will%20also%20help%20to%20keep%20you%20engaged%20in%20what%20you%20are%20invested%20in%20since%20you%20have%20an%20emotional%20attachment%20to%20that%20segment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKovar%20recommended%20that%20people%20look%20at%20their%20retirement%20accounts%20every%206-12%20months%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20risk%20they%20want%20to%20take%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20might%20adjust%20their%20risk%20levels%20based%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20world%20news%2C%20or%20even%20what%20season%20of%20life%20they%20are%20experiencing%2C%20like%20marriage%2C%20kids%2C%20moving%2C%20or%20changing%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20types%20of%20things%20can%20determine%20a%20person's%20aversion%20to%20risk%20and%20can%20help%20them%20edit%20their%20retirement%20account%20to%20reflect%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291c34c38-4449-4b7d-891c-a05fb16b2a14%5C%22%3E3.%20Consider%20changing%20the%20type%20of%20retirement%20account%20you%20use%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20many%20years%20of%20keeping%20cash%20in%20an%20inactive%20401(k)%2C%20I'm%20looking%20to%20move%20that%20money%20into%20a%20different%20retirement%20account%2C%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20my%20SEP%20IRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKovar%20said%20people%20who%20have%20retirement%20accounts%20that%20are%20inactive%20or%20who%20want%20to%20invest